cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Shape-CFD in academic work, please cite it as below."
title: "Shape-CFD: Training-Free Retrieval via PQ-Chamfer Distance and Graph Smoothing"
abstract: >-
  Shape-CFD is a training-free geometric post-processing pipeline that improves
  dense retrieval by treating LLM hidden states as point clouds rather than
  single vectors. The method combines PQ-Chamfer Distance (splitting 4096-d
  vectors into 64×64-d subspaces and aggregating via Chamfer matching),
  Graph Laplacian Smoothing over KNN candidate graphs, and score fusion.
  Evaluated on six BEIR benchmarks (NFCorpus, SciFact, ArguAna, SCIDOCS, FiQA,
  Quora), Shape-CFD achieves up to +136% nDCG@10 improvement over cosine
  baselines on FiQA, and surpasses BGE-large-en-v1.5 on FiQA and SCIDOCS
  without any retrieval-specific training. Implementation is in Rust (NAPI
  bindings for Node.js). The manuscript is under review at Information
  Processing & Management (IPM-D-26-02154).
